A man who grew mammoth five-foot long dreadlocks over nearly two decades has raised hundreds of pounds for charity by cutting them off.

Gareth Robinson from Bournemouth, Dorset, was 16 when he first had his hair twisted and backcombed into the matted coils after struggling to find a style that he liked.

He stuck with the do for 19 years until the knee-length locks were so long he often sat on them by accident.

