Mr Robinson, a medical screener for the Bournemouth air ambulance, said: 'The dreadlocks weighed about 3lbs and it does feel different.

'My hair has been this way since I was 16 so I am still getting used to it. It all started because I was at that age and I couldn’t find any other hairstyle that seemed to suit me.

'At first they were a couple of inches long, and I didn’t expect I would be growing them to almost 5ft years later, but they are pretty much maintenance free.

'When I was younger I put all manner of things on them after following advice from my friends such as wax, egg whites and beer.

'In more recent years it was easier to manage, although washing it could be a two-person affair.

'My partner Jana had to hold it out of the way while I washed my scalp, otherwise they could take three days to dry.

